<h2 id="pir">PIR</h2>

<p>PASSIVE INFRARED SENSOR:</p>

<ul>
  <li>PIR sensors are made of pyroelectric material, which is used to detect the levels of infrared radiation in the surroundings. The way this sensor works is actually quite interesting and is nicely explained <a href="https://learn.adafruit.com/pir-passive-infrared-proximity-motion-sensor/how-pirs-work">here</a>.</li>
  <li>Follow the link to go to the <a href="https://www.epitran.it/ebayDrive/datasheet/44.pdf">datasheet</a>.</li>
</ul>

<p><img src=":/da5ed8d523d142b783bfa523572c0b2b" alt="70e32a17599ed5becda28990c1442cf7.png" /></p>

